Dia. 03 Failure 3
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue255;\red255\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par Well, then how about Black 1?
\par This is one of the 1-2 points. Is it good enough for Black to live?
\par
\par White plays the placement at 2, if Black would play another move, he would live with this one.
\par Therefore \cf1\b 2 is the vital point\cf0\b0 .
\par
\par The idea of playing the vital point at the 1-2 point was good but the \cf2\b direction\cf0\b0  was a \cf2\b bit strange\cf0\b0 .
\par }
